Client pagination only work when the data is already on $scope.

When the page loads I use $http.post to get some book by its ID and it returns an object that contains a property that is a list of the book copies.

These copies are listed on the table which has the pagination plugin but it not loads.

To simulate the issue, go to "http://plnkr.co/edit/fcdXKE?p=preview" and on the script.js change the code:


From this:
```
$scope.displayed = [];
for (var j = 0; j < 50; j++) {
    $scope.displayed.push(createRandomItem());
}
```
to this:
```
$scope.displayed = [];
$timeout(function() { // just to simulate some delay ($http)
    for (var j = 0; j < 50; j++) {
        $scope.displayed.push(createRandomItem());
    }
}, 10)
```

And of course, add the $timeout reference to the function.

AssertionError: A setup function was called after the first request was handled.  This usually indicates a bug in the application where a module was not imported and decorators or other functionality was called too late.
To fix this make sure to import all your view modules, database models and everything related at a central place before the application starts serving requests.

PY FILE
@app.router(...)
def someview():
from flask.ext.qrcode import QRcode
QRcode(app)
return render_template("qr.html",url=request.url)

