I have a model (SocialMediaIdentity) with ForeignKeyAutocompleteAdmin handling the "user" field, which is a ForeignKey to User:

    related_search_fields = {
        'user': ('username', 'email',),
    }

Upgrading from 2.0.7 to 2.0.8 breaks this. Digging through I find that the issue is that model_name has the value "socialmediaidentity" (i.e. the model for which I'm using ForeignKeyAutocompleteAdmin), whereas it should be "user". Thus it looks for username__icontains in the SocialMediaIdentity model instead of in the User model.

